Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 0.6 percent to
4,350.09.  Miners:  Atlas Consolidated Mining & Development (AT)  Corp fell 2.3 percent to 23.25 pesos, ending a four-day, 13
percent rally after the price of copper declined.  Philex Mining
Corp. (PX)  , the nationâ€™s biggest metals producer, fell 0.8
percent to 24.30 pesos.  Copper for delivery in three months slid as much as 0.4
percent to $9,533.50 a metric ton on the London Metal Exchange
today, after falling for two straight days.  East Asia Power Resources Corp. (PWR)   surged 33 percent
to 1.28 pesos, the highest close since Nov. 14, 2000. Century
Properties Inc. completed the purchase of shares in East Asia
Power equivalent to a 93.6 percent stake for 127.4 million pesos
($3 million), a stock exchange filing showed. The shares jumped
